# üìò Product Document

## Social Media Campaign Automation Tool & Revenue CRM

---

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Product Overview

The system is an **AI-assisted social media campaign and lead management platform** that:

* Identifies **viral and high-performing content patterns** by region and niche
* Generates **original, platform-ready campaign content**
* Automates **posting, tracking, and attribution**
* Captures and qualifies **leads into a lightweight CRM**
* Routes **high-intent leads** to:

  * **CodLearn** (DIY / students / prototyping)
  * **Splendid Technology** (custom web apps, e-commerce, automation, AI integrations)

This platform is built **first for internal growth**, then reusable as a **commercial product or managed service**.

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Core Capabilities

### A. Trend Intelligence Engine

* Region-based trend detection (UK, India, Global)
* Multi-source trend ingestion (Google Trends, YouTube, Reddit, social metadata)
* Trend scoring based on:

  * velocity
  * recency
  * engagement indicators
  * niche relevance
* Historical snapshots for momentum tracking
* Output as structured **Trend Intelligence JSON**

---

### B. Campaign Management

* Auto-create campaigns from top trends
* Campaign attributes:

  * region
  * niche (students, small business, e-commerce)
  * objective (lead generation)
  * routing target (CodLearn or Splendid Technology)
* Campaign lifecycle management (active / paused / archived)

---

### C. AI Content Generation

* Original content generation (no copying)
* Platform-specific content packs:

  * hooks
  * short scripts (15‚Äì30 sec)
  * captions
  * hashtags
  * CTA logic
* CTA auto-routing:

  * DIY ‚Üí CodLearn
  * Business / E-commerce ‚Üí Splendid Technology
* Multiple variations per trend for A/B testing
* Human approval workflow before publishing

---

### D. Publishing & Scheduling

* Automated scheduling by platform and region
* Manual or API-based publishing (MVP-friendly)
* Post lifecycle tracking:

  * draft
  * approved
  * scheduled
  * published
  * failed
* Performance metrics capture:

  * views
  * likes
  * comments
  * clicks

---

### E. Lead Capture & Attribution

* UTM-based attribution from every campaign
* Lead capture via:

  * CodLearn app usage
  * Contact forms
  * CTA clicks
* Unified lead identity across platforms
* Anonymous-to-known lead upgrade (email capture later)

---

### F. Lightweight CRM (Revenue-Focused)

* Centralised lead database
* Lead intent classification:

  * student
  * small business
  * e-commerce
  * internal tool
  * agency / enterprise
* Activity timeline (events-based)
* Notes and follow-up tasks
* Simple pipeline status:

  * new
  * contacted
  * qualified
  * proposal
  * won / lost

---

### G. Lead Scoring & Qualification

* Event-based scoring rules
* Automatic lead qualification
* Sales-ready threshold detection
* High-intent signal detection (e.g., export attempts, e-commerce intent)

---

### H. CodLearn Integration

* Track:

  * project creation
  * intent selection
  * export / deploy attempts
* Use CodLearn as:

  * lead magnet
  * qualification engine
* Seamless handoff for production-ready builds

---

### I. Splendid Technology Handoff

* Automatic handoff creation for high-intent leads
* Full context passed:

  * project details
  * campaign source
  * UTM data
* Sales notification & follow-up task creation
* Clear separation:

  * CodLearn = prototyping
  * Splendid Technology = professional execution

---

### J. Automation & Orchestration

* n8n-based workflows for:

  * trend ingestion
  * campaign creation
  * content generation
  * publishing
  * CRM updates
* Webhook-driven architecture
* Fully auditable event flow

---

### K. Analytics & Insights (MVP Level)

* Campaign performance overview
* Lead conversion funnel:

  * views ‚Üí clicks ‚Üí leads ‚Üí qualified ‚Üí revenue
* Region and platform effectiveness
* Content format effectiveness

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Weekly Execution Plan (8-Week Build)

## Current Implementation Status (as of 2026-01-07)

This repo already implements the MVP backend contracts (FastAPI + Postgres) and an importable n8n workflow.

**Backend foundation**
* FastAPI app + SQLAlchemy models + Alembic migrations
* Postgres schema created via Alembic migration `0001` (enums + tables + indexes)
* Campaign slug support via migration `0002`
* Global Bearer API key auth on all `/api/*` routes

**API contracts (aligned to MVP envelopes/status codes)**
* Trends: `/api/trends/ingest`, `/api/trends/top` (ingest upserts items + inserts snapshots)
* Campaigns: `/api/campaigns` (create/list with `{items:[...]}`)
* Content: `/api/content/generate`, `/api/content/{id}/approve`, `/api/content/approved`
* Posts: `/api/posts/schedule`, `/api/posts/update-status`, `/api/posts/metrics`, `/api/posts/recent`
* Leads: `/api/leads/upsert`, `/api/leads` list (filters), `/api/leads/{id}/events|notes|tasks`, `/api/leads/{id}/score/recalculate`
* Handoff: `/api/handoff/create`, `/api/handoff/recent`

**n8n**
* W1 workflow exists and no longer references `/api/trends/fetch`; it uses a placeholder items node and calls `/api/trends/ingest`.

**Remaining gaps (next work)**
* W2 + W3 n8n workflows (approved content ‚Üí scheduling; lead webhooks ‚Üí CRM + handoff)
* Real trend collectors (replace placeholder items) and/or optional `/api/trends/fetch`
* Actual AI content generation (LLM integration) and approval UI (if desired)
* Publishing integration (manual publish is OK for MVP)

---

