---

## Definition of Done (MVP)

The MVP is considered ‚Äúready‚Äù when the following are true:

* Backend can start cleanly and migrations apply successfully (`alembic upgrade head`).
* All `/api/*` endpoints require `Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>` and return `401` when missing/invalid.
* W1 workflow can run end-to-end and results in:
  * trend ingestion + snapshots recorded
  * campaigns created with slugs
  * content packs created (and retrievable via `/api/content/approved` once approved)
* W2 workflow can take approved content packs and create scheduled posts.
* W3 workflow can upsert leads, append events, recalculate score, and create handoffs for sales-ready leads.

### Next

Suggested next work items to keep momentum:
1) Create W2 + W3 n8n workflows for end-to-end automation
2) Replace placeholder trend items with a real collector (Google Trends / Reddit / YouTube)
3) Add a lightweight approval UI (optional) or keep approval in n8n
